33:22.023 --> 33:24.583
It's Virgil.
I was out to dinnerwith Madeline.

33:24.659 --> 33:28.186
I'm sorry.
They must have had eyes on the street.

33:29.664 --> 33:33.623
- [ Chuckles ]
- So, we do this tomorrow at noon.

33:33.702 --> 33:35.636
Ninth Street Bridge.

33:35.704 --> 33:38.605
We'll exchange Virgil forthe $1 0 million.

33:38.673 --> 33:41.437
Everything go well,
you both get to go home alive.

33:41.509 --> 33:43.704
If not--

33:45.680 --> 33:47.545
[ Places Money On Bar]

33:48.550 --> 33:51.348
Enjoy your drink.
[ Chuckles ]

34:08.036 --> 34:10.766
[ Door Opens ]

34:10.839 --> 34:13.501
Calmed your mother down.

34:13.574 --> 34:16.668
I gave her enough sedatives
to knock out a trucker.

34:16.745 --> 34:20.112
Did you ask her
what the hell she was doing out?

34:20.181 --> 34:22.411
I told her to keep him inside.

34:22.484 --> 34:25.043
Oh, go easy on her, Michael.

34:25.120 --> 34:27.554
They snuck out.

34:27.621 --> 34:29.817
A woman needs a little danger.

34:29.891 --> 34:32.860
All right. So what do we do
about the cops and Mason, huh?

34:32.928 --> 34:36.091
Well, I expect they're gonna
be very disappointed...

34:36.164 --> 34:40.157
when they find out we're giving
the money to theJamaicans.

34:40.235 --> 34:42.226
But we don't have any leverage.

34:42.304 --> 34:44.362
They got Virgil's daughter, Mike.

34:44.438 --> 34:47.601
One problem at a time, Sam.

34:47.676 --> 34:50.509
First Virgil, then his daughter.

34:56.518 --> 34:58.986
We could take some ofthe money...

35:00.422 --> 35:02.413
hire her a lawyer.

35:03.758 --> 35:06.386
That could take care ofit.

35:06.461 --> 35:09.259
That could take care of us too.

35:10.799 --> 35:12.960
I doubt they'll miss it, Mike.

35:23.378 --> 35:27.007
[ Cell Phone Ringing]

35:27.082 --> 35:29.073
Hello.

35:29.150 --> 35:32.711
You thinkyou can playwith me,
you son of a bitch? You destroyed all my files.

35:32.787 --> 35:34.778
Oh, it's good to hear from you too.

35:34.856 --> 35:37.347
- I'm right in the middle of something.
- You broke into my room.

35:37.425 --> 35:39.416
I just wanted to get to knowyou better.

35:39.494 --> 35:41.655
Now then, I'm Michael Westen,
and you are?

35:41.730 --> 35:45.427
You don't need my name. I came down here
to bring you a message: Back off.

35:45.500 --> 35:47.991
People get fired all the time.
Leave it alone.

35:48.069 --> 35:50.765
Oh, good. A message from who?

35:50.839 --> 35:53.171
I just wanted to send him
a thankyou note.

35:53.241 --> 35:55.573
- Dream on, pal.
- [ Phone Beeps ]

35:58.747 --> 36:00.738
- Fi.
- Yes?

36:00.815 --> 36:03.943
My new friend just discovered
I paid him a little visit.

36:04.019 --> 36:06.783
- He'll be moving hotels.
- I'll stay on him.

36:17.432 --> 36:19.366
[Michael Narrating]
When something serious is going down...

36:19.434 --> 36:22.062
it's a good idea
to show up nice and early...

36:22.137 --> 36:24.765
soyou can see the ground
and assess the situation.

36:24.839 --> 36:26.773
Mike, I should go.

36:26.841 --> 36:29.571
- Virgil's my buddy. You don't owe him anything.
- They know me and Fi.

36:29.644 --> 36:33.637
Ifyou show up, they'll think something's wrong.
Just cover us and keep an eye out.

36:33.715 --> 36:35.706
All right. Good luck.

36:38.253 --> 36:41.086
It's cute, this loyalty ofSam's.

36:41.156 --> 36:43.818
I ratherlike this side ofhim.

36:43.892 --> 36:46.986
- Thanks for doing this, Fi.
- Oh, I'm not doing this foryou.

36:47.062 --> 36:50.793
I promisedyourmom
I'd bring Virgil back alive.

36:54.002 --> 36:56.232
[ Horn Honks ]

37:03.578 --> 37:06.012
[ Michael]
Hey, they're right on time.

37:06.081 --> 37:08.072
Let's make this trade, make it quick...

37:08.149 --> 37:11.084
- and get out of here
before things get... interesting.
- [ Cell Phone Ringing]

37:11.152 --> 37:12.813
Yeah, Sam.

37:12.887 --> 37:16.118
Your hunch about Mason was right,
'cause he and the boys just showed up.

37:16.191 --> 37:20.093
Yeah, okay. I'm ready for 'em.
Cops are comin'.

37:20.161 --> 37:22.186
All righty then.

37:22.263 --> 37:25.596
[Michael Narrating] When enough people
hateyou, sometimes the onlymove...

37:25.667 --> 37:29.967
is tojust stand in the middle and hope
theykill each other before they killyou.

37:31.172 --> 37:33.470
Hey! Whatyou doing, man?

37:33.541 --> 37:36.374
What are you doing? I said stop it!

37:37.445 --> 37:39.276
Stop it!

37:41.749 --> 37:44.149
[ Michael Narrating] Anyone who's ever
handled large amounts ofcash can tellyou--

37:44.219 --> 37:46.187
it's one ofthe toughest things
in the world to move.

37:46.254 --> 37:49.155
It's heavy and dense dead weight.

37:49.224 --> 37:52.785
If it's on fire, ofcourse,
that complicates things further.

37:52.861 --> 37:54.829
- Freeze!
- Drop it now!

37:54.896 --> 37:58.127
- Hey, you, get back! I said back up!
- Calm down. Calm down.

37:58.199 --> 38:00.360
Boys, boys, boys! Calm down.

38:00.435 --> 38:02.232
We have a little bit of business first.

38:02.303 --> 38:05.898
Andre, let Virgil go.
Andre, let Virgil go!

38:05.974 --> 38:07.839
I'm gonna find you,
and I'm gonna kill you--

38:07.909 --> 38:11.743
I know, I know! And then you'll cut my throat.
I know, I know. Let him go.

38:11.813 --> 38:14.646
Andre, it's the fumes that ignite.
I don't even have to touch it.

38:14.716 --> 38:18.243
Wait, wait, wait! Okay, okay.

38:24.125 --> 38:26.719
Have-- Have you two guys met?

38:26.794 --> 38:28.921
You have a lot to talk about.

38:28.997 --> 38:32.091
Andre, Detective Mason.
Detective Mason, Andre.

38:32.167 --> 38:34.226
- Get down on the ground!
- You ain't a cop. You're a thief!.

38:34.302 --> 38:36.361
- Okay, on the ground!
- You ain't no cop.

38:36.437 --> 38:39.736
- On the ground! Now! Now!
- Call! Call for backup!

38:39.807 --> 38:41.707
Go ahead. You call forbackup!

38:44.579 --> 38:47.241
[ Grunts ]

38:47.315 --> 38:49.783
- [ Gunfire ]
- Go, go, go!

38:53.288 --> 38:55.586
[ Mason ]
Go! Move 'em out! Move 'em out!

38:56.758 --> 38:58.692
Move out! Let's go, let's go!

38:58.760 --> 39:00.591
Don't let it burn!

39:04.098 --> 39:06.760
[ Men Shouting ]

39:15.009 --> 39:18.809
Come on, Mike. I mean, you'd think we'd
be able to keep a little more than this.

39:18.880 --> 39:21.246
- We took what we needed.
- My daughter called.

39:21.316 --> 39:24.251
She's pissed at me, as usual.

39:24.319 --> 39:26.947
But she's home.
They dropped the charges.

39:27.021 --> 39:29.956
Theyhad to, with theJamaicans dead
and the cops injail.

39:30.024 --> 39:33.221
But unfortunately, you're going to have
to get out of town for a while, Virgil.

39:33.294 --> 39:36.593
With this all over the papers, there are still
a few people out there...

39:36.664 --> 39:39.292
who want to put a bullet in you.

39:39.367 --> 39:43.463
- I'll get the boat fixed up
and go down to the Bahamas.
- Great.

39:43.538 --> 39:46.598
You're sureyou're not just trying to
keep me away from your sweet mama?

39:47.875 --> 39:49.672
Hey, Virg. Don't push it.

39:52.780 --> 39:55.772
Okay. I'll go make my good-byes.

39:55.850 --> 39:57.784
Gentlemen.

40:01.723 --> 40:04.283
- I thinkyou're even, Sam.
- Yeah.

40:04.359 --> 40:07.920
Phew. Oh, by the way,
I, uh, made some calls.

40:07.996 --> 40:10.294
Talked to a buddy of mine at the F.B.I.

40:10.365 --> 40:12.959
Looks like I got the Charger back.

40:13.034 --> 40:15.298
Let'sjust call it a thankyou gift.

40:15.370 --> 40:18.168
- You're welcome, Sam.
- [ Chuckles ]

40:18.239 --> 40:20.173
Okay. I need a beer.

40:27.915 --> 40:30.907
[ Michael Narrating] Getting information out
ofsomeone who doesn't want to give it up...

40:30.985 --> 40:35.615
is all about upsetting the target's
emotional balance, impairing theirjudgment.

40:35.690 --> 40:38.284
- F.ear's good for that. Anger's not bad either.
- Hey, buddy.

40:38.359 --> 40:40.987
I thought we could spend
some more time together.

40:41.062 --> 40:44.031
[ Sighs ] You really don't understand
the situation here, do you?

40:44.098 --> 40:46.225
You're out, man. That's it.

40:46.301 --> 40:49.202
- You should be in jail.
-Jail? That's interesting. Whyjail?

40:49.270 --> 40:53.001
- I don't remember ever doing anything jail-worthy.
- Hey, hey, hey.

40:53.074 --> 40:55.338
- Mmm. Mmm.
- Hey, don't get cute.

40:55.410 --> 40:58.573
I want to know why I got burned.
Show me the burn notice. Tell me. Why?

40:58.646 --> 41:00.876
You know damn well why.
I've seen the dossier.

41:00.948 --> 41:04.213
Dossier? I'd like to take a look
at that dossier. You have it on you?

41:04.285 --> 41:08.244
- Get off!. Getyour hands off me.
- Okay. All right. Fine.

41:08.323 --> 41:11.486
[Michael Narrating] Sometimes intelligence
gathering involves sophisticated techniques...

41:11.559 --> 41:14.323
and a lot ofhigh-tech equipment.

41:14.395 --> 41:17.489
But sometimes it's as simple
as picking someone's pocket.

41:17.565 --> 41:19.499
How'd we do?

41:22.437 --> 41:25.270
Good to meet you, Agent Bly.

